Detailed Description

template<class IdTraits, class Cmp = std::less<typename IdTraits::id_type>>
class TREX::utils::list_set< IdTraits, Cmp >

List based generalized set.

Template Parameters:
IdTraits A traits that helps element key extraction
Cmp A comparison functor

This class is a simple generalized implementation of a set/map using a std::list as the internal container.

It relies on the id_mapper class to locate elements

Note:
This implementation is a simple assovciative container. It implies that it ensure that there's one and only one element with a given key
See also:
class id_mapper
Author:
Frederic Py <fpy@mbari.org>

template<class IdTraits, class Cmp = std::less<typename IdTraits::id_type>>
std::pair<iterator, bool> TREX::utils::list_set< IdTraits, Cmp >::insert ( value_type const &  v  )  [inline]

Element insertion.

Parameters:
[in] v An element value

This method Find the position of v in the set and insert it if there is no element with the same key as v

Returns:
A pair with the first element being the iterator pointing to v position in thins set and second a bool which is true if v was inserted and false if an element with the same key as already exist

In the case second is false it is up to the coder to decide whether he wants to overwrite the former value with v or not
